By directing air stream 42 through the print zone 15 as ink drops 38 are ejected during printing, air current disruption system 40 disrupts air currents acting on ink drops 38 during printing, but does not disrupt the intended trajectory of ink drops 38 during printing. As such, undesirable print defects 51, such as “worms,” are avoided without compromising image resolution, printing speed, and/or accommodation of various thickness of print medium. .
